						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall, central shrine, Maṇavāḷēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 4: 975 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This records a gift of 36 sheep for burning a perpetual lamp to god Tiruvēḷvikkuḍi-uḍaiyār by Koṟṟaṉ Kūttaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Sembiyaṉ Ārkkāṭṭuvēḷāṉ of Ārkkāḍu in Ārkkāṭṭu-kūṟṟam.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. XIX No. 108.</p>						

